<div class="callout-body-container callout-body">
<p>There is a famous bug that confuses every beginner.</p>
<p>If you use <code>nextInt()</code> (to read a number) and <strong>immediately</strong> afterwards use <code>nextLine()</code> (to read text), the Scanner will <strong>skip</strong> the text input!</p>
<p><strong>Why?</strong> When you type a number and hit <strong>Enter</strong>, <code>nextInt()</code> takes the number but leaves the ‚ÄúEnter‚Äù key press (newline character) in the memory. The next <code>nextLine()</code> reads that leftover ‚ÄúEnter‚Äù and thinks you finished typing.</p>
<p><strong>The Fix:</strong> Add an extra <code>nextLine()</code> just to consume the leftover ‚ÄúEnter‚Äù.</p>
<div class="code-copy-outer-scaffold"><div class="sourceCode" id="cb5" style="background: #f1f3f5;"><pre class="sourceCode java code-with-copy"><code class="sourceCode java"><span id="cb5-1"><span class="dt" style="color: #AD0000;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">int</span> id <span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">=</span> scanner<span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">.</span><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">nextInt</span><span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">();</span> </span>
<span id="cb5-2"></span>
<span id="cb5-3"><span class="co" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">// Fix: Consume the leftover newline</span></span>
<span id="cb5-4">scanner<span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">.</span><span class="fu" style="color: #4758AB;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">nextLine</span><span class="op" style="color: #5E5E5E;
background-color: null;
font-style: inherit;">();</span> </span>
<span id="cb5-5"></span>
<span id="cb5-6"><span class="bu" style="color: null;
background-color: null;
